4. Biblia Lat. Sixti, 5ti Romae 1590. & Bib. Lat. Clementis 8vi, Romae 1592. if conveniently they could be had; both Popes pretend to Infallibility, and yet their Bibles contradict one another expreſly, and in terminis, an hundred times. But it muſt be remembred, that the Bibles of Clement the Eighth, are many times Printed, and with a Lying (
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) miſcalled Biblia Sixti quinti, Thus, in an Edition at Antwerp in Octavo 1628. The Title is, Bibl. ſacr. Vulgat. Editionis Sixti Pont. Max. Juſſu recognita, and yet 'tis the Bible of Clem. the 8th. So in another Edition at Antwerp 1603. in Fol. and ſo again Coloniae Agrippinae 1666. in eight little Volumes, in Octavo.

Aderant ſolum Epiſcopi 156. ut conſtat ex Graeca hujus Concilii Editione per Vide 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , &c. p. 99. Edita Heidelb. Anno 1591.
Hieronym. Commolinum Heidelbergae Anno 1591. Quamvis Caranza in Summa Conciliorum, p. 297.
